-# Shown when the slug-less /verify_claim entry can't infer which course the
-# exercise is for (the student has several and there's no return-to). Bracketed
-# notes are descriptive COPY stubs, not draft content; course titles are data.
.container.narrow.claim-verification-exercise.claim-verification-exercise--picker
  .claim-verification-exercise__intro
    %h1 [COPY — heading: ask which course this fact-verification exercise is for]
    - if @courses.any?
      %p [COPY — short explanation: we couldn't tell which course, so pick the one you're doing this for]
  - if @courses.any?
    %ul.claim-verification-exercise__course-list
      - @courses.each do |course|
        %li= link_to course.title, "/courses/#{course.slug}/verify_claim"
  - else
    %p.claim-verification-exercise__empty
      [COPY — message shown when the signed-in user is not in any course]
